    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-12-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-12-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="98" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d98">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-12-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 25, 1893</hi>
                        </date>.
                            (Received December 27.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Thompson communicates a notice sent by the insurgents to the Italian
                        admiral of their intention to bombard should they not receive recognition as
                        belligerents; he observes that the engagements with the insurgents have not
                        been enforced by the naval commanding officers and reports that a very
                        perceptible change of feeling in favor of the Government has been created by
                        the proclamation in which Da Gama favors the restoration of the Empire.</p>
            </div>
